Read data

Manipulation check

The manipulation for mindset was successful, as those in the fixed mindset group had a stronger belief that intelligence cannot be changed over time. On the other hand, the mindfulness intervention did not make the participants more mindful.

Mindset manipulation check

  summary()

Dispositional confounders of the manipulation

Dispositional mindset

Those with higher dispositional growth mindset and / or mindfulness were less likely to believe that intelligence cannot be changed over time.

processed_final %>% 
  select(mc_1, mc_3, cams_mean, ms_mean) %>%
  ggplot() +
  aes(y = mc_3, x = ms_mean) +
  geom_point(alpha = .1) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm) +
  labs(x = "Dispositional growth mindset", y = "Statement: \"Your intelligence is an attribute that you cannot change over time\"")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Dispositional mindfulness

Test main outcomes

Number of solved optional exercises

We test the main hypothesis, that is the association of the mindset (fixed vs.growth) and intervention (mindfulness vs.control) with the number of solved optional exercises.

mod_1 <- glm(extra_tasks ~ mindset * intervention, 
           family = "poisson", 
           data = processed_final)

mod_2 <- glm(extra_tasks ~ mindset + intervention, 
             family = "poisson",
             data = processed_final)

Although we found a significant effect of mindset in the expected direction i.e.growth mindset increases the motivation to solve more practice tasks we found that the assumptions for poisson regression are not met. The tests show both overdispersion and zero-inflation, therefore we need to use a model that corrects for these.

# Negative binomial model
mod_3 <- MASS::glm.nb(extra_tasks ~ mindset * intervention,
                      data = processed_final)

# Zero inflated poisson model
mod_4 <- zeroinfl(extra_tasks ~ mindset * intervention, dist = "poisson",
         data = processed_final) 

# Zero inflated negative binomial model (should be used)
mod_5 <- zeroinfl(extra_tasks ~ mindset * intervention, dist = "negbin",
                  data = processed_final)

tab_model(mod_3, mod_4, mod_5, 
          bootstrap = TRUE,

The model that accounts for both overdispersion and zero-inflation does not show a significant effect neither for mindset, nor for the mindfulness.

report(mod_5) %>% 
  summary()

We fitted a zero-inflated negative-binomial model to predict extra_tasks with mindset and intervention. The models explanatory power is weak (R2 = 0.10, adj. R2 = 0.09). The models intercept is at 1.43 (95% CI [1.14, 1.72]). Within this model:

  • The effect of mindset [Growth] is non-significantly positive (beta = 0.21, 95% CI [-0.16, 0.59], p = 0.260, Std. beta = 0.21)
  • The effect of intervention [Mindfulness] is non-significantly negative (beta = -5.87e-03, 95% CI [-0.39, 0.37], p = 0.976, Std. beta = -5.87e-03)
  • The interaction effect of intervention [Mindfulness] on mindset [Growth] is non-significantly negative (beta = -0.13, 95% CI [-0.66, 0.41], p = 0.642, Std. beta = -0.13)
  • The effect of mindset [Growth] is non-significantly positive (beta = 0.05, 95% CI [-0.99, 1.09], p = 0.923, Std. beta = 0.05)
  • The effect of intervention [Mindfulness] is non-significantly positive (beta = 0.06, 95% CI [-1.01, 1.13], p = 0.915, Std. beta = 0.06)
  • The interaction effect of intervention [Mindfulness] on mindset [Growth] is non-significantly negative (beta = -0.04, 95% CI [-1.50, 1.43], p = 0.962, Std. beta = -0.04)

We fitted a linear model to predict iq_real with mindset and intervention. The models explanatory power is very weak (R2 = 3.57e-03, adj. R2 = -4.32e-03). The models intercept is at 0.74 (95% CI [0.70, 0.78]). Within this model:

  • The effect of mindset [Growth] is non-significantly negative (beta = -0.02, 95% CI [-0.07, 0.03], t(379) = -0.62, p = 0.533, Std. beta = -0.09)
  • The effect of intervention [Mindfulness] is non-significantly positive (beta = 2.83e-03, 95% CI [-0.05, 0.05], t(379) = 0.11, p = 0.911, Std. beta = 0.02)
  • The interaction effect of intervention [Mindfulness] on mindset [Growth] is non-significantly negative (beta = -9.11e-03, 95% CI [-0.08, 0.06], t(379) = -0.25, p = 0.800, Std. beta = -0.05)
